Subject: [PATCH 1/4] translate: secure config and ignore runtime data

Stop tracking local runtime artifacts and centralize application path helpers.

This change introduces a user-level runtime path helper, adds ignore rules for
local config and database files, removes the shipped sample key from the config
file, and makes config persistence treat API keys and Z-Library credentials as
encoded-at-rest values instead of plain JSON fields.

The goal is to reduce accidental secret leakage and avoid writing mutable state
back into the source tree.

